1950至1951年[[西藏和平解放|西藏和平解放]]時繼承了中尼邊界的混亂<ref>{{harvp|Office of the Geographer|1965}}: "The exact number of territorial disputes has never been ascertained, but as many as 20 sectors may have been involved. The most serious disputes were located at Rasu (north of Katmandu), Kimathanka in the east, Nara Pass, Tingribode near Mustang, Mount Everest, and the Nelu River. Most of these disputes were settled in favor of Nepal, although several favored China."</ref>。1960年3月21日簽訂了邊界條約，承認傳統習慣線並設立了聯合邊界小組以劃定更準確的邊界<ref name="IBS"/>。邊界劃定完成後，1961年10月5日簽訂最終邊界條約<ref name="IBS">{{Citation
